<!-- .SH "NAME" -->
<A name=>

     <H3>NAME</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
tomoyo-ld-watch - a TOMOYO Linux utility to automatically update library pathnames
<!-- .SH "SYNOPSIS" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=1>

     <H3>SYNOPSIS</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .B tomoyo-ld-watch -->
<B>tomoyo-ld-watch</B> <!-- .SH "DESCRIPTION" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>DESCRIPTION</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
This program appends shared libraries to exception policy automatically when the location of shared libraries in /etc/ld.so.cache has changed. The rules are appended with the "allow_read" directive.
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
Updating packages can cause shared libraries to change. By running this program while updating packages, it is possible to avoid errors due to shared libraries being unreadable.
<!-- .SH "EXAMPLES" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>EXAMPLES</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .B Watch for shared library changes: -->
<B>Watch for shared library changes:</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
tomoyo-ld-watch
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .SH "NOTES" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>NOTES</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Before this program can be invoked, it must be registered in <I>/sys/kernel/security/tomoyo/manager</I>.
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
This program is obsolete. You can run tomoyo-queryd instead of running this program.
